<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="TI2" checkit-title="Integration by parts">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Explain how to find the anti-derivative of <m>f(x)=4 \, x^{3} \sin\left(x\right)</m>.
                    
                </p>
                
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Explain how to evaluate the following definite integral:
                    <me>
                        \int_{ 2 }^{ 7 } 4 \, x^{3} \sin\left(x\right) dx.
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
        
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <m>\displaystyle \int 4 \, x^{3} \sin\left(x\right) dx=-4 \, x^{3} \cos\left(x\right) + 12 \, x^{2} \sin\left(x\right) + 24 \, x \cos\left(x\right) - 24 \, \sin\left(x\right)+C.</m>
                </p>
                
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <m>\displaystyle \int_{ 2 }^{ 7 } 4 \, x^{3} \sin\left(x\right) dx = -1204 \, \cos\left(7\right) - 16 \, \cos\left(2\right) + 564 \, \sin\left(7\right) - 24 \, \sin\left(2\right).</m>
                </p>
                
            </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
